Syntax: clutch

Activates a clutch item held in your left hand. Clutch items are rare,
specially crafted objects with powerful one-time or limited-use magical
effects. Holding the item and typing "clutch" triggers its stored ability.

Clutch item types and their effects:
  - Portal clutch: Opens a portal to a specific room, transporting you
    instantly. The item is consumed on use.
  - Gate clutch: Summons a creature to your location. There is a percentage
    chance the creature will follow you. The item is consumed on use.
  - Some clutch items are not consumed and can be used again.

Restrictions:
  - The clutch item must be worn in the LEFT HAND hold slot.
  - Cannot be used in rooms flagged as NO PORTAL.
  - The item must have a valid clutch type stored in it.

The item must be of type ITEM_CLUTCH. Ordinary held items cannot be
activated with this command.

See also: hold wear remove
